-- Network Rail Said to Add 500 Million Pounds in Linkers Tap
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2012-03-13T13:02:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/network-rail-said-to-add-500-million-pounds-in-linkers-tap.html
Network Rail Infrastructure Finance
Plc is added 115 million pounds to its index-linked notes due
2027, according to a banker involved in the transaction.  The company is also adding 130 million pounds to its 2037
index-linked notes and 255 million pounds to its 2047 notes, the
banker said. The bonds will be priced to yield 30 basis points
more than U.K. government debt.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Martin at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net  